HEADWORD: Pycnodontini
<hw>Pyc`no*don"ti*ni</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos>
<ety>[NL.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>An extinct order of ganoid
fishes. They had a compressed body, covered with dermal ribs
(<xex>pleurolepida</xex>) and with enameled rhomboidal scales.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

